WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:03.687
Whatever we did, we also
brought a baby into this world.

00:03.690 --> 00:05.733
Guilt is hard to overcome...

00:05.736 --> 00:07.617
I wish we had a fresh start.

00:07.620 --> 00:09.246
...in any circumstance...

00:09.249 --> 00:10.995
Like it or not, you and I are gonna be

00:10.998 --> 00:12.123
in each other's lives.

00:12.126 --> 00:13.742
...especially in death...

00:13.745 --> 00:15.710
Jon... I don't want to erase him.

00:15.713 --> 00:16.757
That's understandable.

00:16.760 --> 00:18.960
I haven't been able to
look at Debra's things.

00:18.963 --> 00:20.726
Grief messes with your head.

00:20.729 --> 00:22.188
About the night Chad died.

00:22.191 --> 00:24.233
Eric has your brother's heart.

00:24.236 --> 00:25.487
Did you lose somebody, too?

00:25.490 --> 00:26.718
My fiancÃ©e.

00:26.721 --> 00:28.722
...until it's all you know.

00:28.725 --> 00:30.100
I haven't played since I got sick.

00:30.103 --> 00:32.381
Well, you're not sick
anymore. Open mic night?

00:32.384 --> 00:34.406
So, how do you free yourself...

00:34.409 --> 00:35.546
Maggie?

00:35.549 --> 00:38.509
...without pushing away
the ones you love the most?

00:38.512 --> 00:39.906
I've been fighting with my dad.

00:39.909 --> 00:41.929
We're just so different.

00:41.932 --> 00:43.648
I think Jon might be my father.

00:48.131 --> 00:49.715
I'm just saying, I've been going there

00:49.716 --> 00:51.078
for the better part of six months,

00:51.081 --> 00:52.773
and they have yet to get my name right.

00:52.776 --> 00:56.015
I was Margo. I was Meggy.

00:56.018 --> 00:58.597
At one point, I think I
was Muggy, like I'm weather?

00:59.542 --> 01:01.859
I don't understand why you're
still paying for coffee.

01:01.862 --> 01:02.781
Just do what I do.

01:02.784 --> 01:04.384
Wait for someone to get preoccupied

01:04.387 --> 01:05.555
- with their phone, and...
- Mm-hmm.

01:05.557 --> 01:06.933
...you take your free beverage.

01:08.843 --> 01:10.236
It's delicious.

01:10.237 --> 01:12.468
Something in the latte family.

01:12.471 --> 01:13.712
Suck on that, Muggy.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.195
So, uh...

01:18.198 --> 01:20.085
what did you end up doing last night?

01:20.088 --> 01:21.380
Uh, not much.

01:21.383 --> 01:23.234
I was at my old apartment.

01:24.144 --> 01:25.352
Playing piano.

01:25.355 --> 01:26.856
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

01:26.859 --> 01:28.711
Finally busted out
the old keyboard, huh?

01:28.714 --> 01:29.953
Good for you.

01:29.956 --> 01:31.207
- Yeah.
- Huh.

01:33.119 --> 01:36.246
Well, sounds like a wild night.

01:36.249 --> 01:37.166
Yeah.

01:37.169 --> 01:39.023
Seriously? Colin? Again?

01:39.024 --> 01:40.650
Yeah, he's got his dad's bladder.

01:40.651 --> 01:42.693
Speaking of which,
I'll see you upstairs.

01:43.821 --> 01:44.987
Oh.

01:44.988 --> 01:46.531
Hey, Eric.

01:46.532 --> 01:47.865
Hey.

01:47.866 --> 01:49.700
Um, great news.

01:49.701 --> 01:51.077
I tracked down that sheet music

01:51.078 --> 01:53.079
for that Oasis song
you were looking for.

01:53.080 --> 01:55.623
Oh. You did not have to do that.

01:55.624 --> 01:57.041
Oh, it's no big deal.

01:57.042 --> 01:58.459
That'll be $300.

01:58.460 --> 02:00.044
Seems steep.

02:00.045 --> 02:01.429
Is that before or after

02:01.432 --> 02:04.173
the you've-got-
my-brother's-heart discount?

02:04.174 --> 02:05.800
Uh, well played.

02:05.801 --> 02:08.845
So, um, what happened last night?

02:08.846 --> 02:10.429
You chicken out or something?

02:10.430 --> 02:11.556
What are you talking about?

02:11.557 --> 02:13.599
The open mic. Uh, I saw Gary there.

02:13.600 --> 02:15.226
I figured you were gonna perform.

02:16.293 --> 02:17.627
Gary was there?

02:17.630 --> 02:19.188
Yeah, he poked his head in

02:19.189 --> 02:20.815
for a minute and then took off.

02:20.816 --> 02:23.359
I figured you told him about it.

02:23.360 --> 02:25.695
Uh, no.

02:25.696 --> 02:27.948
He must have... seen the flier.

02:30.159 --> 02:32.117
Yo, Colin!

02:32.120 --> 02:35.079
Mr. Squirrel said his
nuts are bigger than yours.

02:36.373 --> 02:38.416
Whatcha gonna do about it?

02:38.417 --> 02:41.544
Hey, Gare, about the open mic night,

02:41.545 --> 02:42.628
I wanted to talk to you about that.

02:42.629 --> 02:44.101
Where's Colin?

02:44.104 --> 02:46.341
I thought he... followed
you up the stairs.

02:47.634 --> 02:49.427
No, he was with you.
He was on the leash.

02:51.555 --> 02:53.347
Colin!

02:53.348 --> 02:54.808
Colin?!

02:56.308 --> 02:58.184
Colin!

02:58.187 --> 02:59.531
Here, boy!

02:59.534 --> 03:00.688
Colin!

03:00.744 --> 03:01.992
Colin!

03:02.772 --> 03:04.648
- Colin!
- Colin!

03:04.651 --> 03:06.145
Colin!

03:11.533 --> 03:13.534
- Colin!
- Colin?!

03:13.535 --> 03:15.369
Come on, man.

